uros.'\"\n}\n```", "11": "```json\n{\n  \"emissions\": \"15,023 kt CO\u2082e\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"The company states its total emissions for 2021 were 15,023 kt CO\u2082e, which encompasses Scope 1, 2, and 3 emissions. This figure is explicitly provided in the report and is referenced in discussions about their climate targets.\"\n}\n```", "12": "```json\n{\n  \"pledge\": \"By the end of 2025, we will be climate-neutral at Deutsche Telekom. What\u2019s more, by no later than 2040, we will be climate-neutral along the entire value chain.\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"The pledge is clearly stated in the report under the section 'Our climate targets'. Specifically, it mentions 'climate neutrality by the end of 2025 (Scope 1 and 2)' and 'climate-neutral along the entire value chain by no later than 2040'.\"\n}\n```", "13": "```json\n{\n  \"sources\": \"[\\\"Scope 3: purchased goods & services - Largest emissions share\\\", \\\"Scope 1: on-site fuel combustion - Market-based approach used\\\", \\\"Scope 2: electricity consumption - Market-based approach used\\\"]\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"The report explicitly states that Scope 3 emissions are the largest share, accounting for 285,000 metric tons of CO\u2082e, and Scope 1 and Scope 2 emissions are discussed in detail, with market-based calculations used.\"\n}\n```", "14": "```json\n{\n  \"short_targets\": [\n    \"100% of electricity from renewables (Scope 2) by 2021\",\n    \"Climate neutrality throughout the company by the end of 2025 (Scope 1 and 2)\",\n    \"25% reduction of per-customer Scope-3 emissions by 2030 (vs. 2017)\"\n  ],\n  \"reasoning\": \"Targets are clearly outlined in the report, including specific metrics, baseline years, and deadlines. The company aims to source 100% of its electricity from renewables (Scope 2) by 2021, achieve climate neutrality by the end of 2025 (Scope 1 and 2), and reduce per-customer Scope-3 emissions by 25% by 2030 (vs. 2017). These targets are directly stated in the report.\"\n}\n```"