reasoning\": \"The report explicitly states that Scope 3 emissions were 285,000 metric tons of CO\u2082e in 2021, and that most of these emissions occurred in the upstream value chain.\"\n}\n```", "24": "```json\n{\n  \"upstream_scope_3_targets\": [\"none\",],\n  \"reasoning\": \"The report mentions targets for reducing Scope 1, 2, and 3 emissions but does not specify any targets specifically for reducing upstream Scope 3 emissions.\"\n}\n```", "25": "```json\n{\n  \"scope_3_emissions\": \"285,000 metric tons of CO\u2082e\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"The company states that Scope 3 emissions were 285,000 metric tons of CO\u2082e in 2021, representing the largest emissions share compared to Scope 1 and 2 emissions which amounted to around 11,000 metric tons of CO\u2082e. This information is provided in the section discussing Scope 3 emissions.\"\n}\n```", "26": "```json\n{\n  \"scope_3_targets\": [\"reduce per-customer Scope-3 emissions by 25% by 2030 (vs 2017)\", \"achieve net-zero emissions, with no carbon footprint left in any of the three scopes, by the end of 2040 at the latest\"],\n  \"reasoning\": \"The report explicitly states 'plan to achieve a 25 percent reduction per customer in these emissions by 2030 (versus 2017)' and 'plan to achieve net-zero emissions, throughout all three Scopes, by no later than 2040.'\"\n}\n```", "27": "```json\n{\n  \"climate_contributions\": [\"none\"],\n  \"reasoning\": \"The report does not mention any beyond-value-chain contributions, such as donations, investments, or grants to reforestation projects or other environmental initiatives.\"\n}\n```", "28": "```json\n{\n  \"offsetting_claims\": [\"Event Policy specifies the ways in which we offset emissions generated by events.\", \"Offset over 18,000 metric tons of CO\u2082 through various measures.\", \"Around 17,000 metric tons of CO\u2082 were compensated for through renewable energy projects.\", \"A further 1,300 metric tons of CO\u2082 through carbon removal projects.\"],\n  \"re